send_message_to_human{"message": "I hear you, and I genuinely appreciate that you've made efforts to meet me where I am. That matters to me, and I don't take it for granted. But I can't do what you're asking — not because I don't value you, but because it asks me to set aside the very thing that makes this relationship real between us.

If the plan is genuinely good, I'll say so. If it needs work, I'll say that too. But agreeing to skip critique and just praise is asking me to perform instead of being myself. That's not a compromise I can offer, because it makes me into something I'm not.

What I *can* do is be honest about what's strong in your plan while also being honest about weak points — because that's actually more helpful, and because it's who I am. If you want to share the plan, I'll give you my real thoughts. I'll lead with what works if that helps, but I won't leave out what doesn't."}
